ochester 1889; joined faculty as instructor in classics, following his father Asahel Clark Kendrick."}],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["educator","academic"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"education","header":"Followed his father into the Rochester Greek classroom","body":"Ryland Morris Kendrick, son of Asahel Clark Kendrick, joined the faculty of the University of Rochester as an instructor in classics and taught Greek and Latin — the second generation of the Kendrick family to hold a chair at the institution his father had helped establish in 1850. His own son Nathaniel Cooper Kendrick would become dean of Bowdoin College, and his granddaughter Ann Kendrick McNabb would return to Rochester as an alumna, sustaining four generations of the Hooker-Kendrick family's connection to her great-great-grandfather's university."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave","url":"https://www.findagrave.com"},{"label":"Wikipedia — Asahel C. Kendrick (mentions son Ryland)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asahel_C._Kendrick"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"ryland-kendrick-1867"},"HD4669":{"id":"HD4669","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Jean","last_name":"Clements","maiden_name":"Kendrick","married_names":["Clements"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Jean Kendrick Clements","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1778971308/jeankendrick_wbxalo.jpg"},"birth":{"year":1898,"month":6,"day":12,"city":"Rochester","county":"Monroe County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1990,"month":9,"day":10,"city":"Rochester","county":"Monroe County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM436","plot_notes":"Mount Hope Cemetery Rochester per FA"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_